@node P1 "Notes From the Editor"
@toc "menu"

Notes From the Editor
By:  Jason Compton (jcompton@bbs.xnet.com)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

All right, here we are, Issue 2 and plugging along nicely.  I've even kept
my promise to make it AmigaGuide.

Of course, it's still not polished and perfect yet, and I apologize.  I'm
not the greatest at getting around to prettying things up.

Thanks to everyone for sticking with Amiga Report through two of the most
delayed issues in our history.  All I can say is: it'll never happen 
again.  Sorry it did in the first place.

Thanks also to everyone who responded so positively to AR's first
coverdisk.  Hopefully, this issue will keep you just as satisfied.

In other news...nobody has any solid news about Commodore.  Unfortunately.

In AR-related news, Amiga Report was featured (briefly) with a screen
shot in August's Amiga Shopper magazine...I haven't seen it yet, but I'm
told we're mentioned in a brief piece on Internet magazines.  Still, a
screenshot is a screenshot, and as far as I know marks the first time AR's
been mentioned in a true-print publication.  It won't be the last, though,
since I've just accepted an offer to review games for Amiga Game Zone.
Rest assured, I'll do everything I can to promote my "home" magazine.

Keep reading, and enjoy the stuff on the disk.

Jason
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@endnode
