@node P2-1 "Yak 1.59 AR-lite"
@toc "menu"

Feature:  Yak 1.59 AR-lite (Martin W. Scott, Gael Marziou and
Philippe Bastiani)
-------------------------------------------------------------

An excellent "catchall" commodity, sporting several Intuition enhancements,
a screen blanker, keyclicking, no-drive clicking, and more.  "AR lite"
means that I've removed the non-English documentation/catalogs/installs
for space reasons.  Sorry.  (I got clearance to do it...)

@endnode
@node P2-2 "GuidePrefs 1.0"
@toc "menu"

1.  GuidePrefs 1.0 (Bart Vanhaeren)
-----------------------------------

Tired of those old boring buttons in AmigaGuide documents?  Hate the colors?
Spruce them up with GuidePrefs 1.0.  Makes AmigaGuide document-reading a
bit more customizable.

@endnode
@node P2-3 "UPSey 1.1"
@toc "menu"

2.  UPSey 1.1 (Colin F. Thompson)  
---------------------------------

Submitted directly by the author.  UPSey, a commodity, will convert ZIP
codes to UPS Zones.  Useful if you're doing a lot of business with UPS,
obviously.  Does not include cities other than San Diego, but detailed
instructions are included for creating your own databases.

@endnode
@node P2-4 "XenoStar Demo"
@toc "menu"

3.  XenoStar Demo (AGE Entertainment Software)
----------------------------------------------

Remember SiniStar in the arcades?  THIS IS IT.  Well, it's about as close
as it can get, except that the voice isn't QUITE as scary as I remember.
An incredibly fun, incredibly PLAYABLE game.  Don't miss it.

@endnode
@node P2-5 "Reactor"
@toc "menu"

4.  Reactor (Bowie J. Poag)
---------------------------

Instead of the blue picture from last issue, Poag blows something up in
shocking red.  At least, it looks like he's blowing something up.  Done
again in his distinctive style.

@endnode
